The paper discusses the algorithmic technique of set merging and its application to the maximum cardinality matching problem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), game theory (cs.GT), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Among these, cs.DS and cs.DM are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the algorithmic technique and the matching problem discussed in the paper. However, the paper may also be relevant to researchers working in the other sub-categories mentioned above.
